    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hey @caybro @anastasiyaig @igor-sirotin - thanks for looping me in :)\r\n\r\nWe recently finished redesigning Wallet settings, and with it the flows around testnet activation/deactivation. \r\n\r\nAs you'll see from the flows below, we've gone with the amber semantic colour for the new banner design given it is not an error as such as you say (so red is not appropriate) but there is a relevant warning attached to that mode: `In this mode, all blockchain data displayed will come from testnets and all blockchain interactions will be with testnets` which is something very important to remind the user and something for which the other semantic colours wouldnt be suitable for. \r\n\r\nA blue banner would feel a little too informational / passive and green also doesn't feel semantically appropriate.\r\n\r\nWe could consider another colour but other options like purple for example which are distinct from the semantic palette don't feel quite right. \r\n\r\nPerhaps have a quick look and let me know what you think - happy to take suggestions :)\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/idUoxN7OIW2Jpp3PMJ1Rl8/%E2%9A%99%EF%B8%8F-Settings-%7C-Desktop?node-id=15248-319698&t=iprWQUK3VKWNyrls-4\r\n\r\ncc @John-44 ",
